        "id": 1000926
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-15T11:28:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Defaults to empty, which leaves placeholders / raw %L\u003cid\u003e in the output.\n\nI\u0027m not sure of the actual benefit, but specification requires to translate placeholders without bindings too:\n\n\u003e % L\u003cresource-ID\u003e \n\n\u003e The MC-assigned URI of an RDE Provider defined resource (specified by a\n\u003e resource ID within the target PDR), or /invalid.PDR\u003cresource-ID\u003e if\n\u003e unrecognized resource ID\n\nSo it looks like if we don\u0027t have mapping for resource id 123 for example, we need to translate it from `%L123` to `/invalid.PDR123`",
      "revId": "c7fa048ac33ae881daf076b521e2f7b19ca88f8f",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
